description._content: Catalog #: 09_00987 Title: Captain E. Cleon Freeman Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Seven military men onboard the ""Coral Sea"" Typewritten inscription ""With the hope that you remember your shipmates and with kindest personal regards to a brother in arms Col. C. E. Freeman who fully qualifies as an honorary member of the crews of the USS Coral Sea and Battle Carriers Air Group Furi on their shakedown off Cuba in March 1948. H. P. Stone, Capt. US Navy, Cleon Freeman was a Captain of the 110th Air Corps Observation Squadron during World War II and served as a liason officer between the Ninth Air Force and ground forces working in England. He was awarded the Croix de Guerre in 1940 and the Bronze Star Medal in 1944, Tags: Captain E. Cleon Freeman Special Collection Photo,Â 1948 Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
